    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-04T03:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-04T03:13:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1910</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d198fn1">Sent via the Embassy in Japan.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-04T17:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 30, 3.03 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday Soviet notified me they had dissolved City Council and taken over its
                    business. Result cannot be apparent before 8th, as all offices closed till then
                    for Easter holidays.</p>
                <p>All interested posts informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
